We've never been a remove your shoes at the door household but now that we have this new rug from  @enkay.home the rules have changed. It's too special. Do you take off your shoes in your house?
.
If you're looking for a great company to support this is it.
Enkay’s most used raw material, wool, is 100% biodegradable. All of the water from Enkay’s dyeing unit is treated and made safe for human use before it leaves the facility.
All raw colors are Global Organic Textile Standard (GOTS) certified and eco-friendly.
Enkay also brings eye care directly to the villages of its female artisans. With over 250 villages covered. 20,379 individuals benefited from eye screening and 10,344 spectacles have been distributed.
#EnkayHome #gifted

Here are my thoughts on TRENDS. Generally I hate the word. It implies that something is popular now and will be unpopular in a short amount of time. I understand that styles shift and change over time and that's natural but trends are something that tend to be overdone and oversaturate our feeds which is why we develop such strong opinions about them. I  suggest you style your home in a way that makes you happy, do it for yourself and what you love, not what you see all over the internet and whats popular. But, on the other hand, if a trend is something you genuinely love don't be afraid to do it. I know people often say things about trends like "I'm so sick of seeing this everywhere" However, are you really seeing it in your everyday life, in your friends/family/acquaintance homes, or are you just seeing it alllll across your social media feed?? Maybe we're spending too much time scrolling? How saturated is the trend really? Pay attention to your own personal space and how you feel when you're in it. Forget about the internet audience and 'tastemakers'. Trend or not. Just do what YOU love. Trends and the predictions of what's the next big thing and what's out are a waste of time and only meant to make you feel like what you have isn't right anymore and you have to rework your space and spend more money. I'm over it.

Every time I talk about #trichotillomania I wish it was to say I've figured it out.. I haven't. But even when there is no cure, community can be just as beneficial. 
I've had many feelings about it since I started pulling 27 (woah) years ago. Confusion, sadness, anger, frustration, shame, embarrassment, depression, anxiety, desperation, acceptance and indifference (my current state)
My eyeliner is my security blanket to try and camouflage that I have almost no eyelashes but it's really not that big of a deal (most of the time) It used to feel like pulling controlled me and consumed me and was a huge part of my identity. Now it's just a small fraction of who I am, and what really matters is so much more than eyelashes. 
If you're struggling too just remember that. You're so much more.

Morocco will always have my heart. The colors, the textures, food and most importantly, people. This trip was particularly beautiful and, as you know, heartbreaking. All of our travelers have made it home safely, and we continue to check in on our friends who live there.

I love interior design and I love painting murals but what I didn't realize was that my true passion is people. I've always enjoyed introducing friends to each other, hosting girls nights and watching friendships blossom. There's something so special about human connection. After completing our last group trip to Morocco, I've never felt so at peace and satisfied, and ready to do it again. All of the time spent researching every detail from the riads we stayed at, the food we ate, to finding the perfect balance between adventure and relaxation was totally worth it. To bring together such an amazing group of people that just clicked. Watching new friendships bond, sharing secrets with each other and shedding tears when we said goodbye. My heart is full. I hope you'll join the spring 2024 trip. More details coming soon.

Our group trip for Morocco this March just sold out in 1hr 30min. What?! I can't believe it and I'm so beyond excited and grateful. These trips are my passion and I'm putting everything into them along with my friend, who is also our local guide. Thank you for signing up.
I can't wait to meet this new group and we will plan for a September trip as well. Add your email on my website to be notified of future trips.
